Description: US Drum Supply developed Fat Hoops and many of it’s other products after we discovered that NO ONE was making anything, as far as parts.
Headquarters Regions: Midwestern US
Full Description: US Drum Supply developed Fat Hoops and many of it’s other products after we discovered that NO ONE was making anything, as far as parts and hardware,  on a production level, in America. WHAT? We’re the greatest country in the world, why did we stop making things? Well, as an Engineering and design company, we know the truth about the sad story. It’s called “Economic Engineering”, and ” Planned Obsolescence”, but we really don’t have time for the whole thing here. At US Drum Supply, we loathe these practices. We back all of our products with a Limited Lifetime Guarantee. We have spent a lifetime (over 30 years) playing, building, restoring, and otherwise modifying modern drums. It’s always amazes us when we pick up, what is supposedly, the latest, greatest thing in the drum world, and find out from closer inspection, that the company really just found another way to shortcut their manufacturing process.  US Drum Supply is here to turn this manufacturing process around, and start building things better, not Cheaper.                                                         Collectively, our team has over 75 years experience in the Music Industry, Design and Engineering, Manufacturing, Distribution, Marketing and a proven history of successful business operations. This start up company combines the best of the best – They have been hand-picked, stalked, swooned, and even bought a cup of coffee here and there, to bring you a collection of innovative and forward thinking individuals. We are working very hard, and diligently to ensure that US Drum Supply becomes the leader in providing the highest quality, most innovative parts in the world. All of this, while maintaining competitive pricing and unmatched customer service.  We are a music-loving group that will be in tune with each and every customer that seeks our products or services.

It provides videos under different categories like news, sports, entertainment, music and movies. Users can customize All In One Video page by reordering the video channels using the drag and drop feature. Users can select uLinkx popular videos based on today, week, month and all time. uLinkx video search results have been enhanced to allow users to sort search results based on relevance and date. uLinkx new Family Filter feature allow users to filter out videos based on family preferences. uLinkx added support to index current news videos. Users can now view current news videos at a single location. uLinkx had also added an easy way to import YouTube user's videos. uLinkx added video search API to allow partners to take advantage of uLinkx video search technology. Partners can use the API to enable video search and play videos on their web site.  uLinkx, a video search engine for people to search and watch web videos, today opened its service to the masses. Apart from video search, it provides video bookmarking and platform for organizing, socializing and video syndication. uLinkx collects videos from many video sharing web sites, like Youtube, Google videos, MySpace, Metacafe, Yahoo, Revver, Grouper, iFilm, Dailymotion and many more. uLinkx video search engine is self learning as it keeps looking for the relevant videos based on user search and watch patterns. Users can bookmark any video they find on internet using uLinkx bookmarklet, which automatically collects relevant video metadata from popular video hosting websites. Users can do quick local video search on uLinkx and live video search on Youtube, Google, Myspace, Metacafe, Yahoo, Revver and Grouper by clicking on the tabs. uLinkx provides top videos from the web(Youtube, Google, Myspace, Metacafe, Yahoo, Revver) at its home page. Users can also browse through videos based on popularity, popular tags, most recently added and most recently watched videos. uLinkx supports tagging both by letting users associate a set of keywords with the videos/playlist and browse through their tags. By registering, users can share videos, save their favorites, create playlist, comment on the videos/playlist. uLinkx allows users to collect their videos in playlist with different view options- (List, Grid, Show). Users can elect to broadcast their playlist publicly or share them privately with friends and family. uLinkx is building a community that is highly motivated to watch and share videos. At uLinkx user can add other users as friends and find out what their friends are watching. uLinkx provides support for Quicklist and History. uLinkx supports video embedding, which allows users to insert a video clip into myspace, blogs, or other web sites where anyone can watch them. The video clips are not hosted by uLinkx but user can play it on uLinkx using the embedded code from the video source site. At uLinkx users can earn money by providing Google adsense information. uLinkx will show Google ads using their adsense id on playlist and videos collected by them. uLinkx lets user quickly post the video to these bookmarking services like digg, reddit, newsvine, blinklist, delicious, google bookmark and yahoo myweb. uLinkx supports video syndication using widgets and Google gadgets. Users can place uLinkx playlist and search plug-in on their web page or Google personalized page. uLinkx provides comprehensive media RSS feeds which can be used by developers as an API." Description: Saint Francis Medical Center is a school in Trenton.
Headquarters Regions: East Coast, Northeastern US
Full Description: For nearly 150 years, St. Francis Medical Center has been providing quality medical services to residents of its community.  In addition to being a well-established and respected medical facility, today St. Francis is a place of research as well as a place where future doctors complete residencies and where future healthcare professionals obtain training.  In addition to offering residencies to soon-to-be doctors in such areas as Emergency Medicine, Ophthalmology and Dermatology, St. Francis trains and educates future nurses and radiological professionals.  In addition to a two-year RN program, St. Francis offers an LPN to RN bridge program, which is designed for licensed practical nurses who would like to become registered nurses.  The advanced technology found at St. Francis give students in all programs the chance to get hands-on training for their chosen profession with all the current tools of the trade.  A Catholic organization, St. Francis Medical Center also promotes the idea of compassionate loving service to patients. This mindset is integrated into the student curriculum and is also the reason for St. Francis’ community outreach activities.  Admissions requirements differ depending on the program. Admission to the nursing program, for example, requires a high school diploma or GED, submission of transcripts, three recommendation letters and a passing score on the Test of Essential Academic Skills (TEAS). Students increase the likelihood of acceptance if they have an academic background in such subjects as Anatomy and Physiology.  Pell grants, loans and private scholarships are also possible sources of financial aid that students may receive to help with tuition costs. Once enrolled, students must maintain a certain grade point average in order to continue receiving aid.
